This paper discusses a vulnerability analysis framework that utilizes Kolmogorov Complexity estimates to identify system components that are vulnerable. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of a tool that utilizes a growing library of complexity estimators, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the identification of semantic types based on their complexity, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
